other_tests.findings: Enlarged appendix measuring 1.0 cm, hyperenhancing with surrounding inflammatory mesenteric fat stranding and trace free fluid. Coiled configuration with a central rim enhancing fluid collection suggestive of abscess. Punctate calcification in the spleen and liver likely consistent with prior granulomatous disease. No retroperitoneal, mesenteric, portacaval, pelvic sidewall, or inguinal lymphadenopathy evident.
